#   3.17 2026-06-12  Alan W Phillips  Fixed silent scan music (3.16). The
#                                     background looper used an asynchronous MCI
#                                     "play" (no wait) followed by an immediate
#                                     "status mode" poll; without a message pump
#                                     on the worker thread the sequencer never
#                                     sounded, and the instant poll re-triggered
#                                     in a tight loop, so playback was silent
#                                     despite the start message. The worker now
#                                     plays with the blocking "play <alias> wait"
#                                     (the call IpanemaMID.ps1 proves audible),
#                                     rewinding and replaying each pass for the
#                                     loop; Stop-ScanMusic sets the stop flag and
#                                     sends an MCI "stop" from the main thread to
#                                     interrupt the blocking play at once. The
#                                     worker reports open success via a
#                                     $Control.Started flag so Start-ScanMusic can
#                                     fall back to a new Windows Media Player path
#                                     (native loop mode) when the MCI sequencer
#                                     device cannot be opened. Added
#                                     Start-ScanMusicViaMci and
#                                     Start-ScanMusicViaWmp; Start-ScanMusic is now
#                                     a method-selecting orchestrator and
#                                     Stop-ScanMusic dispatches teardown on the
#                                     handle's Method. No change to the scan logic,
#                                     matching rule, reports, or email.
#   3.18 2026-06-14  Alan W Phillips  Added a play-count cap to the menu
#                                     option 6 scan music. The new
#                                     $ScanMusicMaxPlays variable
#                                     (default 5) limits how many times
#                                     the MIDI plays through; if the scan
#                                     finishes first, playback is stopped
#                                     at that point, so whichever comes
#                                     first wins. A value of 0 or less
#                                     restores the pre-3.18 behavior of
#                                     looping until the scan completes.
#                                     The MCI looper now counts each
#                                     clean pass (a stop-interrupted pass
#                                     returns non-zero and is not
#                                     counted) and exits when the cap is
#                                     reached, with the cap carried into
#                                     the worker via the synchronized
#                                     $Control hashtable. The Windows
#                                     Media Player fallback was reworked
#                                     to honor the cap as well: it no
#                                     longer uses WMP native looping but
#                                     runs a counted player on a
#                                     dedicated STA runspace (new
#                                     Get-ScanMusicWmpLooper), and
#                                     Stop-ScanMusic tears that runspace
#                                     down via the shared stop flag. No
#                                     change to the scan logic, matching
#                                     rule, reports, or email.
